---
description: Frontend & mobile wiring rules (apps/web, apps/web-next, apps/mobile)
globs: apps/web/**,apps/web-next/**,apps/mobile/**
---

Full detail: [docs/agents/frontend.md](../../docs/agents/frontend.md) and [docs/MOBILE.md](../../docs/MOBILE.md).

- The frontends and the Expo mobile app are wiring references, not product UI. Each has its own package.json + lockfile.
- No tests here (per project direction) — the 90% floor is backend-only.
- Never store tokens/secrets in localStorage (module memory in the sample; httpOnly-cookie BFF in prod).
- On mobile: access token in memory, refresh token in expo-secure-store — never AsyncStorage.
- API base URL from env (`VITE_API_URL` / Next env / `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`); on web prefer same-origin `/api` via the proxy.
- Don't import `@clevrook/*` backend libs into a frontend or mobile. Keep Dockerfile/railway.json wiring intact (mobile has none — it ships via EAS).
- Exact-pinned deps + committed lockfile; exception: apps/mobile keeps Expo's `~` ranges on expo-*/react-native — bump via `npx expo install`.
